                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDG"
                ],
                "institute": "1USANOT"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment was made using a 5 MV single-",
                "ended Pelletron accelerator at the Nuclear Science",
                "Laboratory of the University of Notre Dame"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Highly ordered pyrolytic graphite with a dimension of",
                "2 cm x 2 cm x 1 mm was used as a target. It was",
                "attached to a water-cooled aluminum holder and fixed",
                "by a round graphite disk with a rectangular hole in",
                "the center"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The silicon detector array consisted of six",
                "YY1-type silicon detectors and one S2-type silicon",
                "detector, covering angles from 102 to 146 deg and 151",
                "to 170 deg in the laboratory frame. Each wedge shaped",
                "YY1 is segmented into 16 strips on the front junction",
                "side. Six detectors formed a lampshade",
                "configuration. The S2 detector was doubled sided and",
                "has 48 rings on the front junction side and 16",
                "segments on the back ohmic side. The solid angle",
                "covered by the detectors was 4.1% of 4Pi for each YY1",
                "detector and 5.4% of 4Pi for the S2 detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For the measurement of the gamma transitions,",
                "high purity germanium detectors was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cross sections at given incident energy was obtained",
                "from thick target yields measurement. It was",
                "extracted from the derivative of thick target",
                "yields measured in multiple small energy steps."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Systematic uncertainty up to 17% dominate",
                "uncertainties at high energy end and include",
                "contributions from",
                "     - detector geometry and efficiency,",
                "     - angular distributions,",
                "     - summing effects",
                "     - thick target approach",
                " Main contribution to uncertainties at low energy end",
                " was lower statistics and relatively higher background"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
